# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# Types:     feat, fix, perf, refactor, docs, test, build, ci, chore, revert
# Scopes:    sound, display, power, wifi, bt, battery, system, media, notify,
#            tools, bot, flows, keyboards, callbacks, runner, config, ci
# Subject:   imperative, present tense; no trailing period; <=72 chars
# Body:      explain *why*, not what; wrap at 72 chars
# Breaking:  add `!` after type/scope (e.g. feat(bot)!: ...) and a
#            `BREAKING CHANGE: ...` footer
#
# Examples:
#   feat(sound): add inline keyboard for volume ± and mute toggle
#   fix(wifi): handle missing en0 on Macs without built-in Wi-Fi
#   feat(power)!: require confirm for shutdown/restart
#     BREAKING CHANGE: destructive power actions now need a second tap
